instructions: On your Android phone or tablet, open the Chrome app . At the top right, tap More and then History . If your address bar is at the bottom, swipe up on the address bar. Tap History . Tap Clear browsing data . Next to "Time range," select how much history you want to delete. To clear everything, tap All time . Check "Browsing history." Uncheck any other data you don't want to delete. Tap Clear data .

On your Android phone or tablet, open the Chrome app . At the top right, tap More and then History . If your address bar is at the bottom, swipe up on the address bar. Tap History . Find the entry you want to delete. To the right, tap Remove .
